BUSINESS ANALYTICAL PROJECT REPORT¶

Objective: The objective of this report is to analyze the data of over 200 road trips by a driver.¶

Description: A driver uses an app to track GPS coordinates as he drives to work and back each day. The app collects the location and elevation data. Data for about 200 trips are summarized in this data set.¶

Data Description:¶

Date: of travel¶

StartTime: when getting into the car¶

DayOfWeek: the day name¶

GoingTo: direction of travel¶

Distance travelled in kilometers¶

MaxSpeed: fastest speed recorded (all trips are on the 407 highway for some portion)¶

AvgSpeed: the average speed for the entire trip¶

AvgMovingSpeed: the average speed recorded only while the car is moving¶

FuelEconomy: a rough estimate of fuel economy (it is inaccurate)¶

TotalTime: duration of the entire trip, in minutes¶

MovingTime: duration when the car was considered to be moving (i.e. not counting traffic delays, accidents, or time while the car is stationary)¶

Take407All: Whether the 407 highway is taken or not.¶

Comments: Comments¶

Data shape: 205 rows and 13 columns¶

Data Source: This data is Kevin Dunn's work.¶

The data is collected from OpenMV.net website.¶

Contact Person : Kevin Dunn¶

Contact details: kgdunn@gmail.com¶

The copyrights belongs to Kevin Dunn but there is no usage restrictions involved in using the data.¶

I want to analyze is there any link with the avgspeed and FuelEconomy. Does speed affects the Fuel Economy?¶

How does taking highway affects the distance?¶

How does destination column GoingTo affects the TotalTime?¶

How does destination column GoingTo affects the Distance?¶

Handling the missing values.¶

There are different ways to handle missing values¶

Some of them are:¶

Drop them all. Meaning to remove them.¶

Replacing with certain values (e.g., mean, mode, median, specific value).¶

Removing unnecessary columns (e.g., Comments: "unnecessary" means those columns are not considered for the analysis. For example, it is obvious that there is no need to analyze "Comments".¶

Some columns missing values can be replaced with a specific value (e.g., mean, median), while replacement is not possible for other columns. When replacement is not possible then it is better to remove the coloumns with missing values but it should be done mindfully.¶

If the coloumns are completely removed without considering it's values may affect the results of the analysis.¶
